This is a small genus with seven named species that are restricted to the Eastern Mediterranean from Greece to Anatolia . The new species collected in Iran represent the southeasternmost records of the genus. Compared to other gnaphosids, homology of the male palpal structures in this genus is unclear, as it is questionable whether the sclerotized hook-like structure (“posterior hook” sensu
Panayiotou et al. 2010
) that guides the tip of the embolus is a greatly modified median apophysis or not. Here, we treat the hook-like structure as a median apophysis.
